### Component 4: Python Backend Logic & Services

#### [MODIFY] [file_processing.py](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Downloads/Lighthub/Project_Sankofa/file_processing.py)
- Implement `extract_text_from_pdf(file_path)` using `pdfplumber` or `pypdf`.
- Implement basic image reading using PIL and optional `pytesseract` OCR, catching errors if Tesseract is not installed locally.
- Implement text chunker with overlap (e.g., recursive character chunking) for vector ingestion.

#### [MODIFY] [ai_logic.py](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Downloads/Lighthub/Project_Sankofa/ai_logic.py)
- Set up ChromaDB local persistent client.
- Implement document namespace creation per course.
- Set up Anthropic Client to call Claude API.
- Implement semantic similarity mappings between outline topics and course content vector database.
- Implement RAG conversation generation using Claude API with retrieved database context.
- Implement Panic Mode generators (producing structured JSON for the 48-hour schedule, flashcards, and study snippets).

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Downloads/Lighthub/Project_Sankofa/app.py)
- Construct FastAPI application with standard CORS setup.
- Define schemas for request/response handling.
- Implement endpoints:
  - `POST /api/upload`: Receives multi-part file uploads (PDF/images) or text outlines, processes them, and indexes them in ChromaDB.
  - `POST /api/chat`: Runs RAG query search and generates conversational response.
  - `POST /api/detect-gaps`: Performs similarity scans between outline topics and course materials to calculate coverage percentage.
  - `POST /api/panic-mode`: Generates 48-hour revision schedules, key summaries, and flashcards.

